50 grams Grated Cheese
2 sachet(s) Mayo
1 pot(s) Ballymaloe Tomato Relish
2 unit(s) Brioche Buns
1000 milliliter(s) Tomato Basil Soup
to taste Oil

Heat the soup per packet instructions
Meanwhile, gently flatten the brioche buns with your hands.
Spread mayo over the cut side of each bun base.
Sprinkle the cheese on top.
Spread the Ballymaloe relish over the cut side of the bun lid and pop on top of the cheese.

Place a large pan over medium heat with a light drizzle of oil.
Once hot, add the toastie and cover with a lid.
Allow the buns to toast and the cheese to melt, pressing down occasionally with a spatula or heavy-bottomed pan, 3-5 mins each side.

Halve the toasties and plate up.
Serve the warm soup alongside.